{verso}
Dear Mr. von Cube!  
Best thanks for your note of August 30. I am very glad that you have recovered from your illness – that, too, belongs to art, which demands a great deal of tension. I shall take active interest in your many beautiful hopes and prospects; may they reach fulfilment in rapid succession! Here it is still very hot, and in spite of this my Free Composition summons me. I send you my best greetings.
